[2026-03-15T16:18:37Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AcGnYryP1XRLSdUY7xEeoF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Evolution System Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the evolution-related code in this Go project. Here's my detailed findings:\n\n### 1. **THE CURATOR** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go`)\n\n**Purpose:** Merges lessons into prompt files using ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) principles.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- **`Apply(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, lesson *Lesson) (*Change, error)`** (lines 18-62)\n  - Reads the current prompt file from disk\n  - Calls the LLM with a system prompt instructing ACE-style curation\n  - System prompt (lines 25-34) specifies:\n    - Append lessons to a \"## Learned Rules\" section\n    - Update existing rules if a lesson refines/duplicates one\n    - Preserve all existing content exactly\n    - Keep rules concise and actionable\n  - User prompt (lines 36-37) contains:\n    - Current prompt content in markdown fence\n    - Lesson insight and suggested action\n  - **Handles LLM responses:**\n    - Calls `stripCodeFences(raw)` (line 44) to extract content between markdown fences\n  - Creates audit snapshot before writing\n  - Writes updated prompt to disk\n  - Returns a `Change` struct with type=\"prompt_update\", snapshot reference\n\n**Code Fence Handling (`stripCodeFences`, lines 67-90):**\n- Trims whitespace from response\n- Finds opening ` ``` ` fence (line 70)\n- If no fence found, returns input unchanged\n- Skips past opening fence and language hint (lines 75-81)\n- Finds closing fence using `LastIndex` (line 84)\n- Returns content between fences (line 89)\n- Handles edge cases: no closing fence, no opening fence, fences malformed\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- Uses `LLMClient` interface (Complete method)\n- Uses `AuditLogger` for snapshots\n- Operates on filesystem directly with `os.ReadFile` and `os.WriteFile`\n\n---\n\n### 2. **THE ORCHESTRATOR** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`)\n\n**Purpose:** Wires all evolution pipeline stages together and manages the overall flow.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- **`Run(ctx context.Context, triggerRunID string, evoStore ports.EvolutionStore, capStore ports.CaptureStore) (*EvolutionResult, error)`** (lines 50-121)\n  - **Stage 1 (Collector):** Calls `o.collector.Collect()` with stores (line 52)\n  - **Stage 2 (Classifier):** Calls `o.classifier.Classify()` (line 58)\n  - **Stage 3 (Reflector):** Calls `o.reflector.Reflect()` with collected data and classification (line 64)\n  - **Stage 4 (Execute branches):** Loop over lessons (line 85)\n    - Routes by `lesson.Category`\n    - For \"prompt_improvement\": calls `o.curator.Apply()` (line 88)\n    - For \"new_step\": calls `o.handleNewStep()` (line 95)\n    - **Line 90 `continue`:** If curator fails, log but continue pipeline (don't fail entire run)\n    - Appends changes to result\n  - **Stage 5 (Audit):** \n    - Updates knowledge base with `o.audit.UpdateKnowledge()` (line 102)\n    - Saves to EvolutionStore if available (lines 107-118)\n\n- **`handleNewStep(ctx context.Context, data *CollectedData, lesson *Lesson, result *EvolutionResult) error`** (lines 124-212)\n  - **Applies lessons that are category \"new_step\"**\n  - Calls `o.scriptGen.Generate()` to create script/prompt file (line 126)\n  - Appends \"add_script\" change to result (lines 131-135)\n  - Reads current workflow file (line 142)\n  - Creates audit snapshot of workflow (line 149)\n  - Derives step name from script path (lines 152-153)\n  - **Determines config** (lines 156-162):\n    - For \"agent\" steps: config[\"prompt\"] = `file(\"path\")`\n    - For \"script\" steps: config[\"run\"] = path\n  - **Adds step to workflow** using `o.mutator.AddStep()` (lines 165-170)\n  - **Wires the new step into graph** (lines 177-188):\n    - Parses updated workflow with `dsl.Parse()` (line 177)\n    - Iterates through existing wires (line 179)\n    - **Finds wire going to \"done\"** (line 180)\n    - **Rewires it through new step** using `o.mutator.RewireResult()` from \"done\" to new step name (line 181)\n    - **Lines 90-91 context:** The `continue` on line 90 of `Run()` means if this whole handler fails, skip it but continue with other lessons\n  - **Adds new wires** for new step's results (lines 191-195):\n    - success -> done\n    - fail -> abort\n  - Writes updated workflow file (line 200)\n  - Appends \"add_step\" change with snapshot (lines 204-209)\n\n**Key Logic:**\n- Uses `dsl.Mutator` for structural changes\n- Uses `os.ReadFile` and `os.WriteFile` for filesystem ops\n- Validates workflow after mutations with `dsl.Parse()` \n- Integrates seamlessly with audit logging and change tracking\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `*Collector`, `*Classifier`, `*Reflector`, `*Curator`, `*ScriptGenerator`\n- `dsl.Mutator`, `AuditLogger`\n- `ports.EvolutionStore`, `ports.CaptureStore`\n\n---\n\n### 3. **THE COLLECTOR** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go`)\n\n**Purpose:** Gathers all data needed for evolution analysis.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- **`Collect(ctx context.Context, evoStore ports.EvolutionStore, capStore ports.CaptureStore) (*CollectedData, error)`** (lines 21-76)\n  - **Step 1 (Knowledge Base):** Reads from `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.md` (lines 30-33)\n  - **Step 2 (Workflow File):** Reads `.cloche/<workflow>.cloche` (lines 35-40)\n  - **Step 3 (Prompt Files):** \n    - Extracts file references using `extractPromptFiles()` regex (line 43)\n    - Reads each prompt file from disk (lines 44-49)\n  - **Step 4 (Runs from Store):** \n    - If evoStore is available (line 52):\n      - Gets last evolution entry (line 54)\n      - **Calls `evoStore.ListRunsSince()`** with sinceRunID (line 57)\n        - This fetches all runs since last evolution pass\n        - Crucial for incremental analysis\n  - **Step 5 (Captures):** \n    - If capStore is available (line 64):\n      - For each run, calls `capStore.GetCaptures()` (line 66)\n      - Stores captures keyed by run ID (line 70)\n\n**Store Usage:**\n- `EvolutionStore.ListRunsSince(ctx, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID)` → `[]*domain.Run`\n  - Port definition at `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` line 58\n  - Returns runs for a project+workflow since a specific run ID\n  - Key for incremental evolution (avoids re-analyzing old data)\n- `EvolutionStore.GetLastEvolution(ctx, projectDir, workflowName)` → `*EvolutionEntry`\n  - Retrieves the last recorded evolution pass\n- `CaptureStore.GetCaptures(ctx, runID)` → `[]*domain.StepExecution`\n  - Retrieves captured execution data for a run\n\n**Data Structures Returned:**\n- `CollectedData`:\n  - `Runs`: list of recent run records\n  - `Captures`: map of run ID → step executions\n  - `KnowledgeBase`: accumulated knowledge as markdown\n  - `CurrentPrompts`: map of prompt file path → content\n  - `CurrentWorkflow`: current DSL content\n  - `WorkflowPath`: path to .cloche file\n  - `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`: scoping info\n\n**Regex Extraction (`extractPromptFiles`, lines 79-91):**\n- Pattern: `` `file\\(\"([^\"]+)\"\\)` ``\n- Finds all file references in workflow DSL\n- Returns unique list (deduplicates with `seen` map)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **INTERFACES THEY DEPEND ON**\n\n**LLMClient** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go` lines 10-12):\n```go\ntype LLMClient interface {\n    Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n- Simple interface for LLM calls\n- Implemented by `CommandLLMClient` (wraps external command like Claude Code)\n\n**Store Interfaces** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`):\n- **EvolutionStore** (lines 55-59):\n  - `SaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error`\n  - `GetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)`\n  - **`ListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)`** ← Key for Collector\n- **CaptureStore** (lines 22-25):\n  - `SaveCapture(ctx context.Context, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error`\n  - **`GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)`** ← Used by Collector\n\n**RunStore** (lines 10-20):\n- Not directly used by evolution, but provides the underlying runs data that EvolutionStore builds on\n\n**Domain Types:**\n- **Run** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`):\n  - `ID`, `WorkflowName`, `State`, `StepExecutions`, `ProjectDir`, `BaseSHA`, etc.\n- **StepExecution**:\n  - `StepName`, `Result`, `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`, `Logs`, `GitRef`\n\n---\n\n### 5. **FULL EXECUTION FLOW**\n\n```\n1. Workflow completes → daemon detects completion\n2. Trigger fires (debounced per project+workflow)\n3. Orchestrator.Run() is called with triggerRunID\n4. Collector.Collect():\n   - ListRunsSince(triggerRunID) → recent runs\n   - GetCaptures(runID) for each → execution details\n   - Reads knowledge base, prompts, workflow from disk\n5. Classifier.Classify() → run category (bug/feature/etc)\n6. Reflector.Reflect() → array of Lessons with metadata\n7. For each Lesson:\n   - if category=\"prompt_improvement\":\n     - Curator.Apply() → reads prompt, calls LLM, strips fences, writes updated prompt\n   - if category=\"new_step\":\n     - ScriptGenerator.Generate() → writes script file\n     - handleNewStep():\n       - mutator.AddStep() → inserts step definition\n       - mutator.RewireResult() → finds wire to \"done\", reroutes through new step\n       - mutator.AddWiring() → adds new step's result wires\n       - os.WriteFile() → saves updated workflow\n8. AuditLogger.UpdateKnowledge() → appends lessons to knowledge base\n9. EvolutionStore.SaveEvolution() → records in DB\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **KEY CODE SNIPPETS & BEHAVIORS**\n\n**Curator's stripCodeFences edge cases (evolution_test.go lines 274-311):**\n- No fences: returns input as-is\n- Language hint: `\\`\\`\\`markdown\\n...\\n\\`\\`\\`` is stripped correctly\n- Commentary: `Here's the updated...\\n\\`\\`\\`\\n...\\n\\`\\`\\`\\nI added...` extracts only middle part\n- No closing fence: returns original (safely falls back)\n\n**Orchestrator's resilience (line 90):**\n- `continue` on error means:\n  - One lesson failure doesn't kill the whole pipeline\n  - Auditing still occurs for successful changes\n  - Partial evolution passes are recorded\n\n**handleNewStep wiring logic (lines 177-188):**\n- Looks for existing wire to \"done\"\n- **Splices new step in** by rewiring that wire through new step\n- Then wires new step's results to terminals\n- Validates with dsl.Parse() after each mutation\n\n**Collector's incremental design:**\n- `ListRunsSince(sinceRunID)` only fetches runs after the trigger point\n- Knowledge base provides long-term memory\n- Avoids re-analyzing stale runs\n\n---\n\n### 7. **TEST FILES COVERAGE**\n\n- **evolution_test.go**: 13 test functions covering:\n  - Collector data gathering\n  - Classifier categorization\n  - Reflector confidence filtering\n  - Curator prompt updates and code fence stripping\n  - ScriptGenerator script creation\n  - CommandLLMClient flag passing\n  - Orchestrator end-to-end with new steps\n  - Workflow validation after mutations\n\n- **trigger_test.go**: 4 test functions covering:\n  - Debounce behavior\n  - Independent project handling\n  - Latest run ID usage\n  - Stop cancellation\n\n---\n\n### 8. **FILE LOCATIONS**\n\nAll files are in `/workspace/internal/evolution/`:\n- `curator.go` - Prompt updates via LLM + code fence stripping\n- `orchestrator.go` - Pipeline orchestration & new step handling\n- `collector.go` - Data gathering from stores & filesystem\n- `types.go` - Type definitions (LLMClient, CollectedData, Lesson, etc)\n- `classifier.go` - Run categorization (bug/feedback/feature/etc)\n- `reflector.go` - Lesson extraction via LLM analysis\n- `scriptgen.go` - New script/prompt generation\n- `audit.go` - Logging, snapshots, knowledge base updates\n- `trigger.go` - Debounce & scheduling\n- `llmclient.go` - CommandLLMClient implementation\n- `evolution_test.go`, `trigger_test.go` - Comprehensive test coverage\n\nInterfaces at `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` and `/workspace/internal/dsl/mutator.go`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a343f11104207acc7 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59155\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 82683</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d40c3d83-4916-4139-bbf3-80547b0a564f","uuid":"f03f159d-6c8b-4f03-93fc-b7518d4163c4","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the evolution-related code in this Go project. I need to understand:\n1. The Curator - its Apply() method, how it handles LLM responses, code fences, etc.\n2. The Orchestrator - its handleNewStep method, how it applies lessons, the continue on line 90-91\n3. The Collector - its ListRunsSince usage, EvolutionStore/CaptureStore usage\n\nFind all files under internal/evolution/ or similar paths. Read the main source files AND existing test files thoroughly. Also look at any interfaces they depend on (ports, stores, etc.).\n\nBe very thorough - read every file completely.","agentId":"a343f11104207acc7","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Evolution System Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the evolution-related code in this Go project. Here's my detailed findings:\n\n### 1. **THE CURATOR** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go`)\n\n**Purpose:** Merges lessons into prompt files using ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) principles.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- **`Apply(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, lesson *Lesson) (*Change, error)`** (lines 18-62)\n  - Reads the current prompt file from disk\n  - Calls the LLM with a system prompt instructing ACE-style curation\n  - System prompt (lines 25-34) specifies:\n    - Append lessons to a \"## Learned Rules\" section\n    - Update existing rules if a lesson refines/duplicates one\n    - Preserve all existing content exactly\n    - Keep rules concise and actionable\n  - User prompt (lines 36-37) contains:\n    - Current prompt content in markdown fence\n    - Lesson insight and suggested action\n  - **Handles LLM responses:**\n    - Calls `stripCodeFences(raw)` (line 44) to extract content between markdown fences\n  - Creates audit snapshot before writing\n  - Writes updated prompt to disk\n  - Returns a `Change` struct with type=\"prompt_update\", snapshot reference\n\n**Code Fence Handling (`stripCodeFences`, lines 67-90):**\n- Trims whitespace from response\n- Finds opening ` ``` ` fence (line 70)\n- If no fence found, returns input unchanged\n- Skips past opening fence and language hint (lines 75-81)\n- Finds closing fence using `LastIndex` (line 84)\n- Returns content between fences (line 89)\n- Handles edge cases: no closing fence, no opening fence, fences malformed\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- Uses `LLMClient` interface (Complete method)\n- Uses `AuditLogger` for snapshots\n- Operates on filesystem directly with `os.ReadFile` and `os.WriteFile`\n\n---\n\n### 2. **THE ORCHESTRATOR** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`)\n\n**Purpose:** Wires all evolution pipeline stages together and manages the overall flow.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- **`Run(ctx context.Context, triggerRunID string, evoStore ports.EvolutionStore, capStore ports.CaptureStore) (*EvolutionResult, error)`** (lines 50-121)\n  - **Stage 1 (Collector):** Calls `o.collector.Collect()` with stores (line 52)\n  - **Stage 2 (Classifier):** Calls `o.classifier.Classify()` (line 58)\n  - **Stage 3 (Reflector):** Calls `o.reflector.Reflect()` with collected data and classification (line 64)\n  - **Stage 4 (Execute branches):** Loop over lessons (line 85)\n    - Routes by `lesson.Category`\n    - For \"prompt_improvement\": calls `o.curator.Apply()` (line 88)\n    - For \"new_step\": calls `o.handleNewStep()` (line 95)\n    - **Line 90 `continue`:** If curator fails, log but continue pipeline (don't fail entire run)\n    - Appends changes to result\n  - **Stage 5 (Audit):** \n    - Updates knowledge base with `o.audit.UpdateKnowledge()` (line 102)\n    - Saves to EvolutionStore if available (lines 107-118)\n\n- **`handleNewStep(ctx context.Context, data *CollectedData, lesson *Lesson, result *EvolutionResult) error`** (lines 124-212)\n  - **Applies lessons that are category \"new_step\"**\n  - Calls `o.scriptGen.Generate()` to create script/prompt file (line 126)\n  - Appends \"add_script\" change to result (lines 131-135)\n  - Reads current workflow file (line 142)\n  - Creates audit snapshot of workflow (line 149)\n  - Derives step name from script path (lines 152-153)\n  - **Determines config** (lines 156-162):\n    - For \"agent\" steps: config[\"prompt\"] = `file(\"path\")`\n    - For \"script\" steps: config[\"run\"] = path\n  - **Adds step to workflow** using `o.mutator.AddStep()` (lines 165-170)\n  - **Wires the new step into graph** (lines 177-188):\n    - Parses updated workflow with `dsl.Parse()` (line 177)\n    - Iterates through existing wires (line 179)\n    - **Finds wire going to \"done\"** (line 180)\n    - **Rewires it through new step** using `o.mutator.RewireResult()` from \"done\" to new step name (line 181)\n    - **Lines 90-91 context:** The `continue` on line 90 of `Run()` means if this whole handler fails, skip it but continue with other lessons\n  - **Adds new wires** for new step's results (lines 191-195):\n    - success -> done\n    - fail -> abort\n  - Writes updated workflow file (line 200)\n  - Appends \"add_step\" change with snapshot (lines 204-209)\n\n**Key Logic:**\n- Uses `dsl.Mutator` for structural changes\n- Uses `os.ReadFile` and `os.WriteFile` for filesystem ops\n- Validates workflow after mutations with `dsl.Parse()` \n- Integrates seamlessly with audit logging and change tracking\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `*Collector`, `*Classifier`, `*Reflector`, `*Curator`, `*ScriptGenerator`\n- `dsl.Mutator`, `AuditLogger`\n- `ports.EvolutionStore`, `ports.CaptureStore`\n\n---\n\n### 3. **THE COLLECTOR** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go`)\n\n**Purpose:** Gathers all data needed for evolution analysis.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- **`Collect(ctx context.Context, evoStore ports.EvolutionStore, capStore ports.CaptureStore) (*CollectedData, error)`** (lines 21-76)\n  - **Step 1 (Knowledge Base):** Reads from `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.md` (lines 30-33)\n  - **Step 2 (Workflow File):** Reads `.cloche/<workflow>.cloche` (lines 35-40)\n  - **Step 3 (Prompt Files):** \n    - Extracts file references using `extractPromptFiles()` regex (line 43)\n    - Reads each prompt file from disk (lines 44-49)\n  - **Step 4 (Runs from Store):** \n    - If evoStore is available (line 52):\n      - Gets last evolution entry (line 54)\n      - **Calls `evoStore.ListRunsSince()`** with sinceRunID (line 57)\n        - This fetches all runs since last evolution pass\n        - Crucial for incremental analysis\n  - **Step 5 (Captures):** \n    - If capStore is available (line 64):\n      - For each run, calls `capStore.GetCaptures()` (line 66)\n      - Stores captures keyed by run ID (line 70)\n\n**Store Usage:**\n- `EvolutionStore.ListRunsSince(ctx, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID)` → `[]*domain.Run`\n  - Port definition at `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` line 58\n  - Returns runs for a project+workflow since a specific run ID\n  - Key for incremental evolution (avoids re-analyzing old data)\n- `EvolutionStore.GetLastEvolution(ctx, projectDir, workflowName)` → `*EvolutionEntry`\n  - Retrieves the last recorded evolution pass\n- `CaptureStore.GetCaptures(ctx, runID)` → `[]*domain.StepExecution`\n  - Retrieves captured execution data for a run\n\n**Data Structures Returned:**\n- `CollectedData`:\n  - `Runs`: list of recent run records\n  - `Captures`: map of run ID → step executions\n  - `KnowledgeBase`: accumulated knowledge as markdown\n  - `CurrentPrompts`: map of prompt file path → content\n  - `CurrentWorkflow`: current DSL content\n  - `WorkflowPath`: path to .cloche file\n  - `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`: scoping info\n\n**Regex Extraction (`extractPromptFiles`, lines 79-91):**\n- Pattern: `` `file\\(\"([^\"]+)\"\\)` ``\n- Finds all file references in workflow DSL\n- Returns unique list (deduplicates with `seen` map)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **INTERFACES THEY DEPEND ON**\n\n**LLMClient** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go` lines 10-12):\n```go\ntype LLMClient interface {\n    Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n- Simple interface for LLM calls\n- Implemented by `CommandLLMClient` (wraps external command like Claude Code)\n\n**Store Interfaces** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`):\n- **EvolutionStore** (lines 55-59):\n  - `SaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error`\n  - `GetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)`\n  - **`ListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)`** ← Key for Collector\n- **CaptureStore** (lines 22-25):\n  - `SaveCapture(ctx context.Context, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error`\n  - **`GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)`** ← Used by Collector\n\n**RunStore** (lines 10-20):\n- Not directly used by evolution, but provides the underlying runs data that EvolutionStore builds on\n\n**Domain Types:**\n- **Run** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`):\n  - `ID`, `WorkflowName`, `State`, `StepExecutions`, `ProjectDir`, `BaseSHA`, etc.\n- **StepExecution**:\n  - `StepName`, `Result`, `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`, `Logs`, `GitRef`\n\n---\n\n### 5. **FULL EXECUTION FLOW**\n\n```\n1. Workflow completes → daemon detects completion\n2. Trigger fires (debounced per project+workflow)\n3. Orchestrator.Run() is called with triggerRunID\n4. Collector.Collect():\n   - ListRunsSince(triggerRunID) → recent runs\n   - GetCaptures(runID) for each → execution details\n   - Reads knowledge base, prompts, workflow from disk\n5. Classifier.Classify() → run category (bug/feature/etc)\n6. Reflector.Reflect() → array of Lessons with metadata\n7. For each Lesson:\n   - if category=\"prompt_improvement\":\n     - Curator.Apply() → reads prompt, calls LLM, strips fences, writes updated prompt\n   - if category=\"new_step\":\n     - ScriptGenerator.Generate() → writes script file\n     - handleNewStep():\n       - mutator.AddStep() → inserts step definition\n       - mutator.RewireResult() → finds wire to \"done\", reroutes through new step\n       - mutator.AddWiring() → adds new step's result wires\n       - os.WriteFile() → saves updated workflow\n8. AuditLogger.UpdateKnowledge() → appends lessons to knowledge base\n9. EvolutionStore.SaveEvolution() → records in DB\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **KEY CODE SNIPPETS & BEHAVIORS**\n\n**Curator's stripCodeFences edge cases (evolution_test.go lines 274-311):**\n- No fences: returns input as-is\n- Language hint: `\\`\\`\\`markdown\\n...\\n\\`\\`\\`` is stripped correctly\n- Commentary: `Here's the updated...\\n\\`\\`\\`\\n...\\n\\`\\`\\`\\nI added...` extracts only middle part\n- No closing fence: returns original (safely falls back)\n\n**Orchestrator's resilience (line 90):**\n- `continue` on error means:\n  - One lesson failure doesn't kill the whole pipeline\n  - Auditing still occurs for successful changes\n  - Partial evolution passes are recorded\n\n**handleNewStep wiring logic (lines 177-188):**\n- Looks for existing wire to \"done\"\n- **Splices new step in** by rewiring that wire through new step\n- Then wires new step's results to terminals\n- Validates with dsl.Parse() after each mutation\n\n**Collector's incremental design:**\n- `ListRunsSince(sinceRunID)` only fetches runs after the trigger point\n- Knowledge base provides long-term memory\n- Avoids re-analyzing stale runs\n\n---\n\n### 7. **TEST FILES COVERAGE**\n\n- **evolution_test.go**: 13 test functions covering:\n  - Collector data gathering\n  - Classifier categorization\n  - Reflector confidence filtering\n  - Curator prompt updates and code fence stripping\n  - ScriptGenerator script creation\n  - CommandLLMClient flag passing\n  - Orchestrator end-to-end with new steps\n  - Workflow validation after mutations\n\n- **trigger_test.go**: 4 test functions covering:\n  - Debounce behavior\n  - Independent project handling\n  - Latest run ID usage\n  - Stop cancellation\n\n---\n\n### 8. **FILE LOCATIONS**\n\nAll files are in `/workspace/internal/evolution/`:\n- `curator.go` - Prompt updates via LLM + code fence stripping\n- `orchestrator.go` - Pipeline orchestration & new step handling\n- `collector.go` - Data gathering from stores & filesystem\n- `types.go` - Type definitions (LLMClient, CollectedData, Lesson, etc)\n- `classifier.go` - Run categorization (bug/feedback/feature/etc)\n- `reflector.go` - Lesson extraction via LLM analysis\n- `scriptgen.go` - New script/prompt generation\n- `audit.go` - Logging, snapshots, knowledge base updates\n- `trigger.go` - Debounce & scheduling\n- `llmclient.go` - CommandLLMClient implementation\n- `evolution_test.go`, `trigger_test.go` - Comprehensive test coverage\n\nInterfaces at `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` and `/workspace/internal/dsl/mutator.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":82683,"totalTokens":59155,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5987,"cache_read_input_tokens":49502,"output_tokens":3665,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5987},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
