[2026-03-15T16:19:44Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L8ZgzZ2fvqejSX1miR3pjK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Self-Evolution System Design\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→Cloche's self-evolution system analyzes workflow run history and user feedback to\n     6→automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows over\n     7→time. It is a daemon-side post-run pipeline that triggers after every workflow\n     8→completion, applies changes directly to project files, and maintains a structured\n     9→audit trail.\n    10→\n    11→The system draws on the ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) framework for prompt\n    12→evolution — treating prompts as structured, itemized playbooks that accumulate\n    13→lessons rather than monolithic documents that get rewritten.\n    14→\n    15→**Scope (this version):** Additive changes only. Prompt updates, new script\n    16→steps, new agent steps, new wiring. No step removal or mutation of existing step\n    17→definitions.\n    18→\n    19→## Architecture\n    20→\n    21→The evolution system is a multi-stage pipeline with three specialized output\n    22→branches. The LLM handles classification, reflection, and content generation.\n    23→Deterministic Go code handles structural manipulation (DSL editing, file I/O,\n    24→audit logging).\n    25→\n    26→```\n    27→                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n    28→                    │         Workflow Run Completes       │\n    29→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    30→                                   │\n    31→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    32→                    │           Collector                  │\n    33→                    │  Gathers: run results, history.log,  │\n    34→                    │  step outputs, knowledge base,       │\n    35→                    │  current prompts + workflow          │\n    36→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    37→                                   │\n    38→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    39→                    │         Classifier (LLM)            │\n    40→                    │  Categorizes run prompt:             │\n    41→                    │  bug | feedback | feature |          │\n    42→                    │  enhancement | chore                 │\n    43→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    44→                                   │\n    45→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    46→                    │         Reflector (LLM)              │\n    47→                    │  ACE-style: examines traces,         │\n    48→                    │  extracts structured lessons          │\n    49→                    │  (bullets with metadata)              │\n    50→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    51→                                   │\n    52→              ┌────────────────────┼────────────────────┐\n    53→              │                    │                     │\n    54→   ┌──────────▼────────┐ ┌────────▼──────────┐ ┌───────▼──────────┐\n    55→   │  Prompt Curator    │ │  Script Generator │ │  DSL Mutator     │\n    56→   │  (LLM + dedup)     │ │  (LLM)            │ │  (Go code)       │\n    57→   │                    │ │                    │ │                   │\n    58→   │  Merges lessons    │ │  Writes new        │ │  Adds steps,     │\n    59→   │  into prompt files │ │  checker/linter    │ │  wiring, collects │\n    60→   │  as structured     │ │  scripts           │ │  to .cloche file  │\n    61→   │  bullets           │ │                    │ │                   │\n    62→   └────────┬───────────┘ └────────┬───────────┘ └───────┬──────────┘\n    63→            │                      │                      │\n    64→            └──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┘\n    65→                                   │\n    66→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    67→                    │         Audit Logger                 │\n    68→                    │  Records all changes + reasons        │\n    69→                    │  Updates knowledge base summary       │\n    70→                    │  Snapshots pre-change state           │\n    71→                    └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n    72→```\n    73→\n    74→The three branches fire independently based on lesson category. A single\n    75→evolution pass may produce changes across multiple branches, or none at all.\n    76→\n    77→## Multi-Project Scoping\n    78→\n    79→The daemon supports multiple concurrent cloche instances across different\n    80→projects (and multiple runs within the same project). Every run record includes\n    81→`project_dir` — the absolute path to the project directory where `cloche run`\n    82→was invoked.\n    83→\n    84→All evolution state is scoped by project_dir + workflow_name:\n    85→- SQLite queries filter by project_dir\n    86→- Knowledge bases live at `<project_dir>/.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.md`\n    87→- Evolution passes for different projects/workflows run independently\n    88→- One evolution pass at a time per project+workflow (mutex)\n    89→\n    90→## Data Collection\n    91→\n    92→### New Signals Captured Per Run\n    93→\n    94→| Signal               | Where captured                        | Notes                          |\n    95→|----------------------|---------------------------------------|--------------------------------|\n    96→| Assembled prompt     | Prompt adapter, before LLM invocation | Full text sent to the agent    |\n    97→| Agent stdout         | Prompt adapter, after agent returns   | Full LLM response              |\n    98→| Run prompt class     | Classifier LLM, post-run             | bug/feedback/feature/etc.      |\n    99→| Retry count per step | Prompt adapter attempt tracking       | Already in filesystem, add to SQLite |\n   100→| Project directory    | CLI sends to daemon via gRPC          | Currently implicit             |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01UFM7x9ZkEjoc1a9sz8V73a","session_id":"0d73752c-6f12-4bd1-98b9-ceef2d13718a","uuid":"ade40ec7-7a41-4de0-bd6e-3424607b484d"}
